What is a class ?

Class is a way to classify so it can be thought of as grouping of things which satisfy a certain criteria.


What is an instance of a class ?

Instance is an example of a class with specific values for the properties. As we mentioned Class outlines classification criteria to classify. Instance is an example with values which match the classification criteria.

Analogy:

 It's like the concept of Species in biology.It helps us understand the complex world around us by classifying living beings. Species defines the shared characteristics of organisms. Homo Sapiens is the species name for Humans i.e the Class for Humans. All humans -7.6 billion are instances of this Class. 